<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1999,2024]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="316" pageId="21" pageNumber="315">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,483,1999,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="315">Justification of the transfer.</emphasis>
O. P.- 
<bibRefCitation author="Cambridge" box="[551,760,1999,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="315" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O. (1869) Catalogue of a collection of Ceylon Araneida lately received from Mr J. Nietner, with descriptions of new species and characters of a new genus. I. Journal of the Linnean Society of London, Zoology, 10, 373 - 397. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1869. tb 00667. x" type="journal article" year="1869">Cambridge (1869)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Malamel &amp; Joseph &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2017" box="[883,977,1999,2024]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Leucauge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="culta" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[883,977,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="315">M. culta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[984,1113,1999,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="315">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1113,1999,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="315">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1182,1296,1999,2024]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="21" pageNumber="315">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, who placed this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[431,567,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Tetragnatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,567,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Tetragnatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely" box="[581,754,151,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Gravely, F. H. (1921) Some Indian spiders of the subfamily Tetragnathinae. Records of the Indian Museum, Calcutta, 22, 423 - 459." type="journal article" year="1921">Gravely (1921)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1841" box="[1171,1280,153,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Leucauge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1280,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Leucauge</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and was later transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Archer, 1951" authorityName="Archer" authorityYear="1951" box="[423,665,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Anopas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[423,507,188,211]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Anopas</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Archer" box="[515,665,188,213]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Archer, A. F. (1951) Studies in the orbweaving spiders (Argiopidae). 1. American Museum Novitates, 1487, 1 - 52." type="journal article" year="1951">Archer, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Currently the species is included in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[1196,1289,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Tylorida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1289,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Tylorida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[151,243,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Tylorida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,243,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Tylorida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chrysanthus 1975)" authorityName="Chrysanthus" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Chrysanthus" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[702,1028,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Anopas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[702,786,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Anopas</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chrysanthus" box="[806,1020,223,248]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Chrysanthus, P. (1975) Further notes on the spiders of New Guinea II (Araneae, Tetragnathidae, Theridiidae). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 140, 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1975">Chrysanthus 1975</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In his original description, O. P.- 
<bibRefCitation author="Cambridge" box="[151,358,260,285]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O. (1869) Catalogue of a collection of Ceylon Araneida lately received from Mr J. Nietner, with descriptions of new species and characters of a new genus. I. Journal of the Linnean Society of London, Zoology, 10, 373 - 397. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1869. tb 00667. x" type="journal article" year="1869">Cambridge (1869)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out the presence of a median spur on the anterior surface of the male chelicerae of this species. In his redescription, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely" box="[489,663,295,320]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Gravely, F. H. (1921) Some Indian spiders of the subfamily Tetragnathinae. Records of the Indian Museum, Calcutta, 22, 423 - 459." type="journal article" year="1921">Gravely (1921)</bibRefCitation>
also noted the presence of cheliceral spur of the male spider. The descriptions of both O. P.-Cambridge and Gravely indicated the presence of a median spur on the anterior surface of the chelicerae of the male spider, which is the characteristic feature of adult male spiders belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kulczynski" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,234,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Mesida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,234,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Mesida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barrion" box="[249,561,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Barrion, A. T. &amp; Litsinger, J. A. (1995) Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia. CAB International, Wallingford, xix + 700 pp." type="book" year="1995">Barrion and Listinger 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez-Padilla" box="[574,973,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" refString="Alvarez-Padilla, F. &amp; Hormiga, G. (2011) Morphological and phylogenetic atlas of the orb-weaving spider family Tetragnathidae (Araneae: Araneoidea). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 162, 713 - 879. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2011.00692. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Álvarez-Padilla and Hormiga 2011</bibRefCitation>
). From this, it is clear that this species is misplaced within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[350,443,439,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Tylorida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[350,443,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Tylorida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and thus should be transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kulczynski" authorityYear="1911" box="[938,1021,439,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Mesida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[938,1021,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="316">Mesida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
